50|$|God's Grace is {{the final}} novel (his eighth) written by American author Bernard Malamud, {{published}} in 1982 by Farrar, Straus and Giroux. The novel focuses on Calvin Cohn, the supposed sole survivor of <b>thermonuclear</b> <b>war</b> and God's second Flood, who attempts to rebuild and perfect civilization amongst the primates that make their way onto a tropical island.|$|E
